it would have ended up eclipsing 'Pan', a novel I hugely admire. He switches from the first-person narrative of earlier novels to a stately, almost distant third person perspective which I found extraordinarily effective. Even though it's told with great simplicity, Hamsun’s eye for detail never faltered, and within only a matter of pages I had the feeling a novel of epic grandeur was on the way. With incredibly rich characters that are always deep in thought or flustered with feelings, the truthful perspective of existence and experience resulted in a tour de force level of thoughtful and textured storytelling. Isak and Inger were characters I didn't want to leave, I miss them already. Growth of the Soil isn’t so much about us as it is the story of where we all came from. Our ancestors, there prosperous dreams, and the deepest yearning for a warm and loving Homecoming. It simply didn't disappoint. Fully deserved landing Hamsun with the Nobel Prize in Literature. For anyone interested in the day to day lives of early settlers this is a beautifully crafted must read.","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/26706841?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"classic-fiction","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/26706841?shelf=classic-fiction"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"scandinavia-nordic","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/26706841?shelf=scandinavia-nordic"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"nobel-laureates","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/26706841?shelf=nobel-laureates"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1613980349"},"likeCount":119,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":24,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.piNwVWAkLDYV0HKORJnl_w":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1